replies.body:
**Wards in this game confuse me. Does everyone get one when they start for free? Also, sometimes when the other team places them they are visible and sometimes they aren't. Why is that.**

There are two types of wards. Green wards{{item:2044}}  and pink wards{{item:2043}} . Green wards cost 75 gold and last 3 minutes unless destroyed by true sight. Pink wards last until killed and provide something really important, true sight.  True sight is there to help "clean" spaces from enemy wards and, some champions have the ability to go invisible and this true sight ability let you spot them. Green wards last like 3 seconds visible when put so if the enemy sees it go down, they can use their true sight to clean it. 

Everyone get a trinket at the start that can put a weaker ward for 1 minute, there are useful for lanning and spotting early ganks, but should be switched to the other trinkets as soon as needed

**What does the beetle that walks up and down the river do, and why is it there? Is it a moving ward? If so how come my team never has one.**

The beetle is a "jungle" monster per se that spawns and if your team kills it, gives vision of two important objectives, dragon and baron. They also provide a speed boost to the owner team that walks in it. If your team does not have one it means that your team isnt killing the beetle fast enough.

**Can someone explain the difference between the different types of damage. All i understand is Attack Damange and Ability Power, but what about magic? Or is ability power magic? Also what items do you want to build to counter**

There are two types of dmg in the game aside from true damage. Attack damage and Magic Damage. Attack damage is boosted by attack damage items ( surprise!!) and magic damage is  boosted by ability power. Different champions get bonuses from different stats. If you are an Attack Damage Carry (ADC) you benefit from attack damage and those items, and vice versa if you are and Ability Power Carry.

**What is the little red light and circle that appear in areas sometimes. Almost like some type of scouting mechanism but i can't tell if thats an ability or a way to find wards.**

The little red light is a trinket (the red one){{item:3341}}  that lets you have true sight of an area for a few seconds. It lets you spot wards and clear them. The blue circle{{item:3342}}  on the other hand, is a tool to grant vision of an area from afar. Think of a blink dagger for vision in dota terms.

**How many buffs are there? Is it the carry that should get the Buff camps, or should the jungler?**

There are 4 types of general buffs and many more from the jungle.

The main 4 types of buffs are:

Blue buff: This is granted by the blue golem in each jungle and grants lower cooldowns and more mana regenration. It is usually given to the midlaners because they usually use a lot of mana and rely on their spells.

Red buff: Granted by the red golem in each jungle, grants a slowing attack and thus is good for chasing or orb-walking out of enemies range.

Dragon Buff: These are actually a group of 5 buffs granted everytime you kill the dragon.  they grant movespeed damage and all sorts of goodies, so its good to get it.

Baron Buff:  this buff is one of the best buff in the game and is given by killin Baron Nashor. it grants a faster recall, more powerful minions and a speed boost after recalling. This is usually a win condition and the team with it usually wins. It also gives 300g to everyone, so it is awesome

**Is there an item like black king bar which when activated, makes you invulnerable to magic damage, and un-targetable?**

There is no such thing as BKB in the game, but there are alternatives. Zhonya's Hourglass{{item:3157}}  makes you untargetable and unkillable for 2 seconds but you cant move attack or do anything.

Quick Silver Sash{{item:3140}}  and its upgrade lets you get out of 1 stun.slow, snare or whatnot on a 45 second cooldown if i recall correctly.

**What is the strongest damage item in the game? Is there a weapon like Divine Rapier which grants a LOT of dmg, but drops if killed?**

No divine rapier, but there are 7 "high" tier damage items that most carries will build with some variation.

These are:

Attack damage:
Essence Reaver{{item:3508}} 
Infinity Edge{{item:3031}} 
Bloodthirster{{item:3072}} 
Mercurial Scimitar{{item:3139}} 

Ability Power:
Luden' Echo{{item:3285}} 
Zhonya's Hourglass{{item:3157}} 
Rabbadon Deathcap{{item:3089}} 


**Is the whole Rune system more beneficial to someone who pays for runes? Like a pay to win type of thing?**

No such thing. Every rune is the same for everyone. Grind them games and you will be rewarded. Buy the greater runes (those available after lvl 20) the others are not worth it.

**Is the cookie cutter laneing- 1 top, 1 mid, 1 jung, 2 bot? If not what is the standard? and what are some other way to lane?**

The cookie cutter is as you stated, 1 top 1 mid 1 jungle and 2 support. There IS a meta reason of why this is though, if you want I could tell you why. SOme other lane match ups an be seen on super pro scenes so you dont need to worry about them now.

**What's the best website for build guides for Summoners?**

Mobafire and Solomid or something like that...

**How hard is it to solo que and get to Plat or diamond?**

I'm on the struggle in silver 2 just promoted yay. I will carry my way to gold/plat by the end of the season i hope. You need to be skilled and willing to roflstomp every game. Seriously. EVERY GAME.

**I want to learn how to jungle, how do i know who is a jungler and who's not?**

